			<h1>{{page-title}}</h1>
	
			<p>
			Kiva is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit registered in the state of California. Self-sustainability is critical to our work, connecting people through lending to alleviate poverty around the globe. To that effort, we believe that it’s imperative to have a financial model which promotes sustainability, transparency and effectiveness.
			</p>
			<h2>100% of your loans go to the field!</h2>
			<p>That’s right, Kiva doesn't make money on the loans we facilitate through our website and 100% of the funds lenders contribute to loans go to supporting the borrowers they choose. We also don't charge any interest to our Field Partners on the funds we send them.</p>
			<blockquote>“Neither Kiva nor Kiva lenders make any money from the loans they facilitate. Because of this, Kiva is able to partner with groups based on social motive, rather than profit motive.”
				<cite><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/global-development-professionals-network/2014/jun/10/crowdfunding-for-development" target="_blank">The Guardian</a></cite>
			</blockquote>
			<h2>How does Kiva support its operations?</h2>
			<p>We support ourselves primarily through the support of our lender community, who can choose to make optional donations in addition to the loans they make. We also raise funds through grants, interest earned on our bank accounts, corporate sponsors and foundations. This model of fundraising helps promote sustainability, by keeping our fundraising costs low and tapping into the power of the crowd to help cover our costs.</p>
			
			
			
			
			
